                        <p align="left" class="style7">What Do We Provide?</p>

                        <p align="left" class="style3">As a team member, you will be provided with all the resources needed for you to have an enjoyable and amazing ballroom experience. We understand that people enjoy dancing at different intensity levels. Feel free to take advantage of all or just a few of our benefits.</p>

                        <p align="left" class="style3">Currently, our semester dues are $55. For that amount you will receive:</p>

                        <p align="left" class="style3">1) A two-hour lesson with our professional instructors every Saturday from 4:30-6:30 pm in the CCRB mirror room. </p>

                      <p align="left" class="style3">2) Membership to the Ballroom Dance Club, which meets every Sunday. Your membership gets you into all three levels of dance lessons offered by the Club and into their open dance event.<br />

                      For more information about the club and to see their schedule,<span style="font-style: italic"> <a href="http://www.umich.edu/~umbdc/home.htm" target="_blank">click here</a></span>.</p>

                        <p align="left" class="style3">3) Access to practice space at Dance Theater Studio (DTS), conveniently located on N. University above Sushi.come  Monday through Thursday evenings. Mondays are Thursdays are usually coached by upper level team members and review material covered in the Saturday lessons.</p>

                <p align="left" class="style3">4) Amazing intangibles such as befriending team members from all skill levels and recieving helpful dance tips and advice from our best dancers!<br>

                          <br>

                          By becoming a member of our team, you will have the opportunity to  learn and practice ballroom dance almost every single day of the week. How much you decide to invest in the team is entirely up to you. We&rsquo;re sure you&rsquo;ll find the members of this team both friendly and welcoming. The success of our team depends on new members like you every semester, so we hope to see you at our free lessons and recruitment events!</p>

                        <p><span class="style3">Feel free to browse our website in order to get more information. Visiting our FAQ section may help answer some other questions that you may have. </span><br>

                        </p>

